<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1303,1472]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">
These two species can be clearly differentiated by the morphology of apical setae of antenna endopodite. 
<taxonomicName box="[1320,1436,1303,1326]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Acroperus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1320,1436,1303,1326]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Acroperus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is rare in South-East Asia, its populations are found in lakes, associated with vegetation. 
<bibRefCitation author="Idris" box="[1205,1342,1339,1364]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" refString="Idris, B. A. G. (1983) Freshwater zooplankton of Malaysia (Crustacea: Cladocera). Perenbit University, Pertanian, Malaysia, 153 pp." type="book" year="1983">Idris (1983)</bibRefCitation>
did not provide description of antenna for 
<taxonomicName box="[549,753,1375,1399]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Acroperus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="harpae">
<emphasis box="[549,753,1375,1399]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Acroperus harpae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and it is impossible to verify his identification. In book of 
<bibRefCitation author="Maiphae" box="[151,339,1411,1436]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" refString="Maiphae, S. (2014) A Taxonomic Guide to the Common Cladocerans in Peninsular Thailand. Edited by K. Van Damme. Princess MahaChakri Sirindhorn Natural History Museum, Faculty of Science, Prince of Songkla University. O. S. Printing House Co., Ltd. Bangkok. 240 pp." type="book" year="2014">Maiphae (2014)</bibRefCitation>
drawing of 
<taxonomicName box="[500,711,1411,1435]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Acroperus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="harpae">
<emphasis box="[500,711,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Acroperus harpae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to male of 
<taxonomicName box="[975,1216,1411,1435]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Disparalona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamata">
<emphasis box="[975,1216,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Disparalona hamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and drawings of postabdomen and and posteroventral corner of valves, to 
<taxonomicName authority="Thanh, 1980" authorityName="Thanh" authorityYear="1980" box="[792,1245,1447,1472]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Camptocercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vietnamnsis">
<emphasis box="[792,1092,1448,1471]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Camptocercus vietnamnsis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Thanh" box="[1099,1245,1447,1472]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" refString="Thanh, D. N., Bay, T. C. &amp; Mien, F. V. (1980) Key to freshwater invertebrates of North Uietnam. Hanoi, 570 pp. [in Vietnamese]" type="book" year="1980">Thanh, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
